end_memory_text: We talked a bit about the areas we live. Then we talked about hiking, her dislike of it and my enjoyment. How growing up in a different environment affected out views on it.
rest_of_day_open: The next week will mostly involve filling out forms for government agencies to get covid assistance. I don't have many plans except for going to my shifts at the library. I may talk to a few friends, and probably play a few games when I am not busy. Not much is going on.
critical_positive: We had a few things in common that we were able to latch on and talk about. She was a very nice person, and very polite. The objects and pets in the background helped to give us something to talk about as well. We were both introverted, so we both understand about the pauses.
critical_negative: We were both introverts, so we had a lot of pauses. There were times where we had to struggle to find things to talk about. We both seemed to be counting the minutes until the end, not from a lack of enjoyment, but from lack of social energy. With her it felt a bit more like I was prying into her life by asking things.
